15. Nc6+ Bxc6 16. dxc6 Nc5 17. Bh4 Bf8 18. Bc4 Ra7 19. Bd5 $16 {Until here
it's all theoretical, as you can see in the theory section. Now Black's
position is very difficult to defend, because White has a very simple plan and
Black has difficulties in preventing it or in creating a plan of his own.} a5
20. Re3 {As I said in the theory section, White's plan is to double or treble
forces on the open "e" file. So now you can see how, from knowing the typical
opening plans, we can easily understand the moves of a strong GM.} (20. f5 $1 {
Looks more accurate, controls important squares, opens the diagonal for the
queen. And, as I said before: what can Black do?} Qc8 21. Bf3 $1 Qxf5 22. Rd5
$1 Qc8 23. Rxd6+ {Winning! You can see the difference between f5 and the move
made in the game. In this particular line you don't need to hurry up. It's
better to go slowly but surely. In this game GM Kotronias is hurrying up.})
20... Qc8 {Leaving the c7 square for Black's king.} 21. Rde1 {Simply following
the plan.} Qf5 22. Bxf6+ gxf6 23. Re8+ Kc7 24. Qf3 $14 {White has finished his
plan, but not in the most accurate way.} h5 25. Kb1 {The 'always useful' move
in the Sicilian. But in this particular case, 25.Bxf7 was more accurate.} Bg7
26. Rxh8 Bxh8 27. Bxf7 {White has two pawns for the sacrificed piece and a
better position.} Kb6 28. Bxh5 {Three pawns.} (28. Bd5 {Was also very good.})
28... a4 {Looking for some counterplay.} 29. Bg4 Qh7 30. c7 $6 {This move is
not necessary.} (30. Qd5 Qh4 31. Re8 Qxg4 32. Qxd6 Rc7 33. Rb8+ Ka6 34. Ra8+
$11) 30... Rxc7 31. Qd5 f5 $6 {Better was} (31... b3 $1 $11) 32. Qxd6+ Rc6 33.
Qd8+ $6 (33. Qb8+) 33... Qc7 34. Qxh8 (34. Qxc7+ Kxc7 35. Bxf5 a3 36. bxa3 bxa3
) 34... fxg4 35. Qd4 Kb5 36. b3 axb3 $6 (36... Qd6 $1 {Gives Black a slight
advantage! Black need the pawn on a3 in some lines - thats why it's better for
Black mantain the flexibility.}) 37. axb3 Qd6 38. Qc4+ Ka5 39. Re5 $14 Qd1+ $6
40. Ka2 Qd6 $6 41. Rd5 $18 Qc7 42. f5 Kb6 43. Qxb4+ Ka7 44. Qd4 $18 {The thing
I want you to look in this game is that you should not hurry up in this
positions. They require accurate calculation and clear ideas. So remember, if
you want to become a great player in this line, you should work on your
calculations a lot.} 1-0

